cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with detecting actions in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel framework that models the temporal structure of each action instance, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a temporal action proposal scheme, which involves multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. The paper also uses a discriminative model to distinguish positive proposals from background or incomplete ones, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing techniques to describe the proposed method, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
